### Generate OTP

The endpoint triggers an HTTP POST request to generate a one-time password (OTP) for the provided email address.

#### **Access Control:**

- **Role Required:** No Role Required


#### Request Body

- email (string): The email address for which the OTP needs to be generated.


#### Response Body

The response will be in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "id": {
    "type": "integer"
  },
  "email": {
    "type": "string"
  },
  "otp": {
    "type": "string"
  },
  "createdDateTime": {
    "type": "string",
    "format": "date-time"
  }
}

 ```

# Auth Login

This endpoint allows users to authenticate and obtain a token for accessing protected resources.

## Request

- Method: POST

- URL: `http://localhost:8080/auth/login`

- Body:

    - `username` (text, required): The username of the user.

    - `password` (text, required): The password of the user.


## Response

The response is in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "roles": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "token": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response contains the following fields:

- `id`: The unique identifier of the user.

- `roles`: The roles assigned to the user.

- `token`: The authentication token for accessing protected resources.
